      • createKeyValueFields

        public static List<DataField> createKeyValueFields(List<DataField> keyFields,
                                                   List<DataField> valueFields,
                                                   int maxKeyId)
        Create key-value fields, we need to add a const value to the id of value field to ensure that they are consistent when compared by field id. For example, there are two table with key value fields as follows
        • Table1 key fields: 1->a, 2->b, 3->c; value fields: 0->value_count
        • Table2 key fields: 1->c, 3->d, 4->a, 5->b; value fields: 0->value_count

        We will use 5 as maxKeyId, and create fields for Table1/Table2 as follows

        • Table1 fields: 1->a, 2->b, 3->c, 6->seq, 7->kind, 8->value_count
        • Table2 fields: 1->c, 3->d, 4->a, 5->b, 6->seq, 7->kind, 8->value_count

        Then we can compare these two table fields with the field id.

        Parameters:
        keyFields - the key fields
        valueFields - the value fields
        maxKeyId - the max key id
        Returns:
        the table fields
